zation of nanometer size electronic and optical devices the ability to engineer materials at the atomic level has opened myriad possibilities for the advancement of technologies that impact the areas of semiconductors telecommunications chemistry and pharmaceuticals his current research is aimed at the development of si based microphotonic functionality and plasmonic devices that can manipulate the flow of light at the nanoscale research interests nanoscale electronic and photonic materials and devices guiding and manipulation of light in metal optic structures optical properties of semiconductor nanocrystals and nanowires fundamentals of ion beam modification of materials nanoscale thermal engineering with light last modified tue 7 feb 2012 at 18 48 publications title author s journal date surface plasmon polariton analogue to young& 039 s double slit experiment rashid zia mark l brongersma nature nanotechnology 2007 view publication omni directional light emission via surface plasmon polaritons john sq liu mark l brongersma appl phys lett 2007 view publication thin film patterning by surface plasmon induced thermocapillarity lars ra ntzsch karl heinz heinig jon a schuller mark l brongersma appl phys lett 2007 view publication design of midinfrared photodetectors enhanced by surface plasmons on grating structures zongfu yu georgios veronis shanhui fan mark l brongersma optics letters 2006 view publication tunable light emission from quantum confined excitons in tisi2 catalyzed silicon nanowires alex r guichard david n barsic shashank sharma theodore i kamins mark l brongersma nanoletters 2006 view publication plasmonics the next chip scale technology rashid zia jon a schuller mark l brongersma materials today 2006 view publication plasmon assisted chemical vapor deposition david a boyd leslie greengard mark brongersma mohamed y el naggar david g goodwin nanoletters 2006 view publication metal dielectric slot waveguide structures for the propagation of surface plasm